MBOMBELA &#8211; I&#8217;langa Mall&#8217;s general manager, Sandi Human, said rumours of a floor collapsing are untrue.&#8220;At the back of the lifts where the temporary tailor was located, a slab was brought down for the preparation of building the Toys R Us and the expansion of Studio 88. It may have been the cause of the rumours,&#8221; she said.&#8220;Shopping centres have a life cycle and when enough demand is created, it warrants expansion.&#8221;She added that there were many exciting developments in the pipeline.The new Toys R Us store will be a double storey.Also read: I langa Mall s expansion nearing its endMall management have closed off the area where the construction is taking place.